  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractClient
    The AbstractClient contains all the methods necessary to set up the client side of a client-server architecture.
    AbstractServer
    The AbstractServer class maintains a thread that waits for connection attempts from clients.
    AdaptableClient
    The AdaptableClient is a class that extends the AbstractClient in place of the ObservableClient .
    AdaptableServer
    The AdaptableServer is an adapter class that extends the AbstractServer class in place of the AbstractObservableServer .
    AppConfig
    Class defines global configuration for client side
    ChatClient
    Class that handles the chat of client with server
    ChatIF
    This interface implements the abstract method used to display objects onto the client or server UIs.
    ChooseRegionPopUpController
    This class is responsible for providing the functionality for the choose region pop-up window in the GUI.
    ClientController
    Class that implements the ChatIF ocsf interface, handles the connection with server
    ClientsReportController
    This class is responsible for providing the functionality for the clients report screen in the GUI.

    The start class of application
    ConfirmOnlineOrderController

    ConnectionToClient

    CreateNewSaleController

    ObservableServer

    OrdersReportController
